The paper deals with decoding linear codes over finite fields, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). The construction of valid inequalities for the codeword polytope involves combinatorial optimization techniques, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of dynamic programming, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The search for redundant parity-checks is a topic in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), and the development of an efficient decoder is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
